word_mean_info__list.difference: 使用广泛，既可指思想上的计划，又可指任何形式的书面计划或规划。
多指由个人或集体为进行某项工作或完成某一项较大的任务，而制定的计划方案或设想。
普通用词，比plan更强调计划的通盘筹划和某些细节的精心安排。在现代英语中，常用于指阴谋诡计。
最普通常用词，多指事先经过较充分的准备或考虑后制定的计划，也可指非决定性的打算或设想。
从本义蓝图，引申指详细而具体的行动计划。
侧重指按照目标、目的意向，根据固定格式精心作出的计划或安排。
主要指为实现某一阴谋而拟定秘密的计划。

list.abstract: Microsoft Project(或 MSPROJ)是一个国际上享有盛誉的通用的项目管理工具软件，凝集了许多成熟的项目管理现代理论和方法，可以帮助项目管理者实现时间、资源、成本的计划、控制。

号称当代爵士中的"流行乐手"爵士钢琴家DavidBenoit与集电子合成乐大成的RussFreeman携手合作的专辑《TheBenoitFreemanProject》。他们是属于70年代的大师，而当时他们的音乐已和正统的爵士出现了明显的差距，甚至开始被卫道人士斥为非正统的爵士乐，但平易近人的乐风，一般听众接受度高，适合各年龄层，且动人的轻音乐中仍保有爵士乐原有的轻松愉悦、无拘无束、宽广无际的旋律，直到现在，他们仍在乐坛中蓬勃发展，新作品不断的推出。

yingyinNormal.en: The seventh's test of my robotics project.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是我机器人项目的第七次检测。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, I saw you working on your art project.
yingyinNormal.zh: 可是我看到你做你的艺术课项目了。

yingyinNormal.en: Sadly, I'm no longer associated with that project.
yingyinNormal.zh: 很遗憾，我已经被项目团队踢出来了。

yingyinNormal.en: This is where another innovative engineering project comes in.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这就要谈到一个革故鼎新的工程项目。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, I'm no longer working with them. They denied my project.
yingyinNormal.zh: 噢，我已经不在那里混了，他们拒绝了我的项目。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, I would, but we need to make a push on the air force project.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我愿意去，可我们明天要赶工弄一下空军的项目。

yingyinNormal.en: This is Tadashi Hamada. And this is the first test of my robotics project.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我是滨田正，这是我机器人项目的第一次检测。

yingyinNormal.en: Thanks. Wow, working on a top secret government project, that is so cool.
yingyinNormal.zh: 谢谢。为政府研发最高机密的项目，那真是太酷了。

yingyinNormal.en: Tadashi Hamada again. And this is the 33rd test of my robotics project.
yingyinNormal.zh: 还是我，滨田正，这是我机器人项目的第三十三次检测。

yingyinNormal.en: Hi. I'm Dr. Sheldon Cooper. I'm the actual brains behind this project.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你好，我是谢尔顿·库珀博士，我才是这个项目的主力设计者。

yingyinNormal.en: Wait till I Snapchat that my friends might be working on a top secret government project.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我要发条朋友圈，说我的好朋友们为政府的机密项目做事。

yingyinNormal.en: This little Macintosh side project has gotten out of hand, Steve, way beyond the pale.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这个小麦金塔项目已经失控了，史蒂夫，我们已经到了亏损的边缘

yingyinNormal.en: I mean, how would you feel if I let Leonard take over your super-asymmetry project? That's funny.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果我让莱纳德接手你的超非对称性项目你怎么想？笑死人了。

yingyinNormal.en: Sorry I'm late. I'm working on a project that may take me up on the next space shuttle.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不好意思，我来迟了，我正在攻关一个项目，可能要上一次航天飞机了。

yingyinNormal.en: You know, what you need to do is put this Air Force project behind you and just dive into something new.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你现在要做的就是忘掉这个空军项目把精力投入新的研究。

yingyinNormal.en: And we're gonna kill every other project. Everything. This company will not make shit anymore.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们会砍掉所有其它的项目，所有的。这个公司再也不会制造什么垃圾产品了

yingyinNormal.en: I'm sorry, I was reassigned to this project. I was told you were taking a temporary sabbatical to focus on other work.
yingyinNormal.zh: 抱歉，我被分配到这个项目。他们说你要暂时休假去忙别的研究。

yingyinNormal.en: You got me removed from my own project? Yeah, and it wasn't easy. Apparently, you're very difficult to replace.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你让我被自己的项目撤下来了？对，而且一点都不容易。显然你很难被取代。

yingyinNormal.en: It's okay, everything's here. Hey, what's going on? You won't believe it; the military confiscated our project.
yingyinNormal.zh: 没事，一切都在。发生什么事了？说了你们也不会信。军方没收了我们整个项目。

yingyinNormal.en: What is this? The notes from our quantum cognition project. I thought we could spend the evening grinding away on it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是什么？我们量子认知项目的笔记。我想着今晚我们可以好好学习[摩擦]一番。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 意为“项目计划”，强调为试验而提出的工作或研究计划，通常规模较大，有时仅指设想的甚至实际的规划。
意为“计划”，强调按照目标或目的而进行的详细完备的设计、计划，着重强调计划的条理性、完善或完美和谐性。
意为“计划，方案”，表示对细节内容进行系统仔细地选择排列之后做出的计划，有时用表格形式表现出来，还可表示某人的狡猾欺诈或对私利的追求。
意为“规划”，表示通常指各部分区分清晰，比例严格的设计。

examination_example.sentence: "The <highlight>project</highlight> has two sides, " says Xavier Serra, Neuritis <highlight>project</highlight> manager and researcher at the University of Barcelona.

examination_example.sentence: Although sites like Kickstarter take all comers, platforms such as Experiment.com and Petridish.org only present scientific <highlight>projects</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 虽然Kickstarter等网站来者不拒，但Experiment.com和Petridish.org这样的平台只展示科学项目。

examination_example.sentence: Crowd funding, raising money for a <highlight>project</highlight> through online appeals, has taken off in recent years for everything from making movies to producing water-saving gadgets.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 近年来，从制作电影到生产节水小工具，通过网络呼吁为一个项目筹集资金的众筹已经在各个领域兴起。

examination_example.sentence: For another, they present the <highlight>project</highlight> with a funny video because good visuals and a sense of humor improved success.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 另一方面，他们用一个有趣的视频展示这个项目，因为好的视觉效果和幽默感增加了成功的概率。

examination_example.sentence: For one, they use a crowd funding platform that specializes in raising money for science, and not just any kind of <highlight>project</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 首先，他们使用一个专门为科学筹款的众筹平台，而不仅仅是任何种类的项目。

examination_example.sentence: Most of them engage with potential donors, since <highlight>projects</highlight> that answered questions from interested donors fared better. And they target a small amount of money.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们中的大多数都与潜在捐助者进行接触，因为回答感兴趣的捐助者问题的项目进展得更好。并且他们的目标金额不多。

examination_example.sentence: Other factors may also significantly influence a <highlight>project</highlight>'s success, most notably, the size of a scientist's personal and professional networks, and how much a researcher promotes a <highlight>project</highlight> on their own.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 其他因素也可能对一个项目的成功产生重大影响，其中最重要的是，科学家的个人和专业网络的规模，以及一个研究员自己推动一个项目的程度。

examination_example.sentence: The more money a <highlight>project</highlight> sought, the lower the chance it reached its goal, the researchers found.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 研究人员发现，一个项目寻求的资金越多，它达到目标的几率就越低。

examination_example.sentence: The <highlight>projects</highlight> included in the study raised S4000 on average, with 30% receiving less than $1000.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这项研究中的项目平均筹集了4000美元，其中30%的项目不到1000美元。

examination_example.sentence: Rather than saying, ‘ This is science, over here is history, 'I see schools taking this idea of <highlight>projects</highlight> and looking at: How do they support children in higher level learning?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我想象学校将不再说“这是科学，这是历史”，而是采纳“项目”这一概念并思考一个问题：如何帮助孩子进行更高层次的学习？

examination_example.sentence: The difference lies in whether the <highlight>project</highlight> is in a sense defined and developed by the student or whether it's assigned by a teacher.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 区别在于项目是否某种意义上由学生制定、开发，或者说项目是否由老师布置。

examination_example.sentence: The <highlight>project</highlight> is called Writing On It All, and it's a participatory writing <highlight>project</highlight> and artistic experiment that has happened on Governor's Island every summer since 2013.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这项活动名叫 Writing On It All，是一个参与式写作项目和艺术实验，自2013年以来每年夏天都会在总督岛举行。

examination_example.sentence: The earliest research report on the five-second rule is attributed to Jillian Clarke, a high school student participating in a research <highlight>project</highlight> at the University of Illinois.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 关于五秒规则的最早的研究报告归功于 Jillian Clarke，一个在伊利诺伊大学(University of Illinois)参加研究项目的高中生。

examination_example.sentence: A vertical solar <highlight>project</highlight> on such a large scale has never been repeated since.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如此大规模的垂直太阳能项目从那以后再也没有出现过。

examination_example.sentence: Covering a skyscraper with solar panels had never been done before, and the CIS tower was chosen as one of the "10 best green energy <highlight>projects</highlight>".
examination_example.sentence_trans: 以前从未有人用太阳能电池板覆盖摩天大楼，所以CIS塔被选为“十大最佳绿色能源项目”之一。

examination_example.sentence: For a long time after this renovation <highlight>project</highlight>, it was the tallest building in the United Kingdom, but it was eventually overtaken by the Mill bank Tower.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在这个改造项目之后的很长一段时间里，它是英国最高的建筑，但最终被米尔银行大厦(Mill bank Tower)超越。

sense_info_list.en: estimate or forecast something on the basis of present trends

examination_example.sentence: If you factor in the <highlight>projected</highlight> rates of technological change, either your skills will become unnecessary, or your industry outdated.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果将技术的预计变革速率考虑在内，要么你的技能变得多余，要么你所在的行业将会过时。

examination_example.sentence: Yet the cost we <highlight>project</highlight> for saving civilization would amount to less than $200 billion a year, 1∕6 of current global military spending.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 然而，我们预计拯救文明的成本每年不到2000亿美元，是目前全球军队费用开支的1∕6。

sense_info_list.en: throw or cause to move forward or outward
make a projection on a plane surface

examination_example.sentence: The <highlight>project</highlight> also resulted in a reduction in the amount of medicines used to perform medical-imaging (医学影像) procedures.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 该项目还导致用于进行医疗成像程序的药物数量减少。

examination_example.sentence: A trial <highlight>project</highlight> by the Montreal Children's Hospital suggested that the use of medical hypnosis (催眠) can reduce pain and anxiety in patients.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 蒙特利尔儿童医院的一个试验项目表明，使用医学催眠可以减轻病人的痛苦和焦虑。

examination_example.sentence: One of the results produced by the trial <highlight>project</highlight> is less use of certain medicines.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 该试验项目产生的结果之一是减少了某些药物的使用。

examination_example.sentence: In all, 80 examinations were conducted for the <highlight>project</highlight> between January and September, 2019, focusing on the imaging procedures that would cause anxiety.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 2019年1月至9月，该项目共进行了80次检查，重点是可能引起焦虑的成像程序。

examination_example.sentence: We were informed about our semester  <highlight>project</highlight> of volunteering at a non-profit organization.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们得知，我们的学期项目是在一个非营利组织做志愿者。

examination_example.sentence: I had only focused on the fact that it was another school <highlight>project</highlight> and one I wanted to get a good grade on.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我只注意到这是学校的另一个项目，我想拿个好成绩。

examination_example.sentence: Researchers in many areas have <highlight>projected</highlight> the widespread collapse as "a credible scenario (情景) this century".
examination_example.sentence_trans: 许多领域的研究人员都将大范围的坍塌预测为“本世纪可信的情景”。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 最普通常用词，多指事先经过较充分的准备或考虑后制定的计划，也可指非决定性的打算或设想。
多指由个人或集体为进行某项工作或完成某一项较大的任务，而制定的计划方案或设想。
使用广泛，既可指思想上的计划，又可指任何形式的书面计划或规划。
